                        "definition": "Investment expenditures incurred per capita.",
                      
                        "unit": "PLN",
                      
                        "dimensions": "total",
                      
                        "methodology": "Investment outlays are financial or material outlays aimed at creating new fixed assets or improving (rebuilding, expanding, reconstructing or modernizing) existing fixed assets, as well as outlays on the so-called initial investment equipment. Investment outlays are divided into outlays on fixed assets and other outlays. Outlays on fixed assets are outlays on: - buildings and structures (including buildings and premises as well as civil and water engineering structures) including, among others, construction and assembly works, - design and cost documentation, - machines, technical devices and tools (including instruments, movables and equipment), - means of transport.",
                      
